{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifies a function to be called at normal program termination."}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/atexit(func:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"metadata":{"platforms":[],"title":"atexit(func:)","symbolKind":"func","roleHeading":"Function","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"atexit"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"func","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GVoidFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GVoidFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib6atexit4funcyyyXCSg_tF"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"atexit","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"func","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GVoidFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GVoidFunc"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since GLib 2.8.2, on Windows "},{"code":"g_atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" actually is a preprocessor"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"macro that maps to a call to the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"atexit()"},{"type":"text","text":" function in the C"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"library. This means that in case the code that calls ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_atexit()"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"i.e. "},{"code":"atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", is in a DLL, the function will be called when the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"DLL is detached from the program. This typically makes more sense"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than that the function is called when the GLib DLL is detached,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"which happened earlier when ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_atexit()"},{"type":"text","text":" was a function in the GLib"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"DLL.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The behaviour of ","type":"text"},{"code":"atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in the context of dynamically loaded"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"modules is not formally specified and varies wildly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On POSIX systems, calling "},{"code":"g_atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" (or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"atexit()"},{"text":") in a dynamically","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"loaded module which is unloaded before the program terminates might"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"well cause a crash at program exit."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some POSIX systems implement "},{"code":"atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" like Windows, and have each"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"dynamically loaded module maintain an own atexit chain that is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"called when the module is unloaded."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On other POSIX systems, before a dynamically loaded module is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"unloaded, the registered atexit functions (if any) residing in that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"module are called, regardless where the code that registered them"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"resided. This is presumably the most robust approach."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As can be seen from the above, for portability it’s best to avoid","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calling "},{"code":"g_atexit()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"atexit()"},{"text":") except in the main executable of a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"program."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"atexit is deprecated:"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is best to avoid g_atexit().","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/atexit(func:)"]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/atexit(func:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifies a function to be called at normal program termination."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"atexit","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"func","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GVoidFunc","text":"GVoidFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"title":"atexit(func:)","deprecated":true,"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/atexit(func:)","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/atexit(func:)"}}}